<h1>All About Chocolate</h1>
<h2>The Best Chocolate Cake Recipe Ever</h2>

<p>
The best chocolate cake recipe – A one bowl chocolate cake recipe that is quick,
easy, and delicious!
</p>

<p>
The best chocolate cake recipe ever? There are plenty of claims for the best
chocolate cake recipe. I get that. But with one bite of this decadent,
moist chocolate cake with chocolate frosting, every single person around
the table commented that this has the best chocolate cake they’d ever tasted.
</p>

<p>
This is by far the best chocolate cake you will ever make. I wish I came up
with this recipe but I stole it from a website called Add a Pinch.
</p>

<h3>Ingredients</h3>

<ul>
       <li>2 cups all-purpose flour</li>
        <li>2 cups sugar</li>
        <li>3/4 cup unsweetened cocoa powder</li>
        <li>2 teaspoons baking powder</li>
        <li>1 1/2 teaspoons baking soda</li>
        <li>1 teaspoon salt</li>
        <li>1 teaspoon espresso powder (optional)</li>
        <li>1 cup milk, buttermilk, almond, or coconut milk</li>
        <li>1/2 cup vegetable oil, canola oil, or melted coconut oil</li>
        <li>2 large eggs</li>
        <li>2 teaspoons vanilla extract</li>
        <li>1 cup boiling water</li>
    </ul>

<h3>Instructions</h3>
<ol>
        <li>Preheat oven to 350°F. Prepare two 9-inch cake pans.</li>
        <li>
            Add flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda, salt, and espresso
            powder to a large bowl and whisk together.
        </li>
        <li>
            Add milk, oil, eggs, and vanilla. Mix on medium speed until combined.
        </li>
        <li>
            Carefully add boiling water and mix until smooth.
        </li>
        <li>
            Divide batter evenly between the pans and bake for 35–38 minutes.
        </li>
        <li>
            Cool cakes for 10 minutes, remove from pans, and cool completely.
        </li>
        <li>Frost with chocolate buttercream frosting.</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Nutritional Information</h3>

    <p>Calories: 124 kcal</p>
    <p>Carbohydrates: 27 g</p>
    <p>Protein: 3 g</p>
    <p>Fat: 1 g</p>

